=== interface/required_api.md ===
# Required public API (interoperability surface) — pretty-clean

The clean crate must expose these entry points so the open side can wire it in
behind thin adapters that translate the live `tamarin_parser::ast` /
closed-theory values into the crate's own AST subset. Every function returns
text that is byte-identical to the oracle's no-prove theory echo for the
corresponding fragment. Names are indicative; the boundary that matters is
"one entry point per observable sub-target, each independently gate-checkable".

```rust
// ── (top) whole theory echo: `theory <name> begin … end` (minus the wf
//    comment and the Generated-from stamp, which are appended by callers). ──
pub fn render_theory(thy: &Theory, sig: &Signature) -> String;

// ── (a) signature block: builtins / functions / equations declarations ──
pub fn render_signature_block(sig: &Signature) -> String;

// ── (b) macros / predicates blocks ──
pub fn render_macros(macros: &[Macro]) -> String;        // "macros: …"
pub fn render_predicates(preds: &[Predicate]) -> String; // "predicates: …"

// ── (c) rule rendering: one multiset-rewrite rule, plus fact & TERM render ──
pub fn render_rule(rule: &Rule, variants: Option<&AcVariants>) -> String;
pub fn render_fact(fact: &Fact) -> String;               // `Foo( a, b )`
pub fn render_term(term: &Term) -> String;               // THE deep core

// ── (d) restriction / lemma FORMULA rendering ──
pub fn render_restriction(r: &Restriction) -> String;
pub fn render_lemma(l: &Lemma, guarded: Option<&Guarded>) -> String;
pub fn render_formula(f: &Formula) -> String;            // ∀ ∃ ⇒ ∧ ∨ ¬ @ ⊏ …

// Layout primitive (BSD-provenance, NOT part of the GPL-erasure surface):
// the HughesPJ `Doc` engine + combinators. Reuse the graphdot cluster's
// clean-room engine (workspace/graph-clean/src/pretty.rs, derived from
// sanctioned/pretty-1.1.3.6). Width = 110, ribbon = 73 for the theory echo.
```

`Theory`, `Term`, `Fact`, `Formula`, `Atom`, `Rule`, `Lemma`, `Restriction`,
`Macro`, `Predicate`, `VarSpec`, `SortHint`, `BinOp`: see `ast_types.rs`.

`Signature`, `AcVariants`, `Guarded` are pre-computed inputs supplied by the
ported closure/solver (SPEC.md "Solver-entangled inputs"); the clean crate
only RENDERS them, and their observable text is learned from the oracle.

=== interface/ast_types.rs ===
// INTEROPERABILITY HEADER (dirty-room provided, expression-stripped):
// type surface of the parsed-theory data model the THEORY PRETTY-PRINTER
// consumes as its render INPUT. Comments and all impl bodies removed.
// Provided solely so the clean implementation can compile against the
// existing data model at integration time.
//
// This is the SAME parsed-AST surface the wellformedness cluster used; the
// pretty-printer walks more of it (every `Term` operator in `BinOp`, `Fact`
// argument lists, `Formula`/`Atom` for lemma & restriction rendering). The
// clean implementer may define their OWN minimal subset for unit testing
// (write test values as Rust constructors, verify against the oracle) and
// only needs this exact shape to drop into the workspace at integration.
//
// NOT in this file (fed to the renderer PRE-COMPUTED by the ported closure /
// solver — see SPEC.md "Solver-entangled inputs"):
//   * the CLOSED signature model (merged builtin + user function symbols and
//     rewrite rules, canonically sorted) that the `functions:`/`equations:`
//     block renders — observable is the emitted declaration text;
//   * per-rule AC-variant substitutions (`variants (modulo AC)` block);
//   * the guarded-formula negation shown in the `/* guarded formula
//     characterizing all counter-examples */` comment under each lemma;
//   * proof skeletons / proof methods (only rendered under --prove; NOT on
//     the no-prove echo the acceptance gate observes).



#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq)]
pub struct Theory {
    pub is_diff: bool,
    pub name: String,
    pub configuration: Option<String>,
    pub items: Vec<TheoryItem>,
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq)]
pub enum TheoryItem {
    Builtins(Vec<String>),
    Functions(Vec<FunctionDecl>),
    Equations { convergent: bool, eqs: Vec<Equation> },
    Macros(Vec<Macro>),
    Predicates(Vec<Predicate>),
    Options(Vec<String>),
    Heuristic(String),
    Tactic(Tactic),
    Restriction(Restriction),
    LegacyAxiom(Restriction),
    Rule(Rule),
    IntrRule(Rule),
    Lemma(Lemma),
    DiffLemma(DiffLemma),
    AccLemma(AccLemma),
    CaseTest(CaseTest),
    ProcessDef(ProcessDef),
    TopLevelProcess(Process),
    EquivLemma(Process, Process),
    DiffEquivLemma(Process),
    Export { tag: String, body: String },
    FormalComment { header: String, body: String },
    Define(String),
    Include(String),
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq)]
pub struct FunctionDecl {
    pub name: String,
    pub arg_types: Vec<Option<String>>,
    pub out_type: Option<String>,
    pub private: bool,
    pub destructor: bool,
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq)]
pub struct Equation {
    pub lhs: Term,
    pub rhs: Term,
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq)]
pub struct Macro {
    pub name: String,
    pub args: Vec<VarSpec>,
    pub body: Term,
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq)]
pub struct Predicate {
    pub fact: Fact,
    pub formula: Formula,
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq)]
pub struct Restriction {
    pub name: String,
    pub formula: Formula,
    pub attributes: Vec<RestrictionAttr>,
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq)]
pub enum RestrictionAttr {
    LeftRestriction,
    RightRestriction,
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq)]
pub struct Rule {
    pub name: String,
    pub modulo: Option<String>,
    pub attributes: Vec<RuleAttr>,
    pub let_block: Vec<LetBinding>,
    pub premises: Vec<Fact>,
    pub actions: Vec<Fact>,
    pub conclusions: Vec<Fact>,
    pub embedded_restrictions: Vec<Formula>,
    pub variants: Vec<Rule>,
    pub left_right: Option<(Box<Rule>, Box<Rule>)>,
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq)]
pub enum RuleAttr {
    Color(String),
    NoDerivCheck,
    Role(String),
    IsSapicRule,
    Process(String),
    External(String, Option<String>),
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq)]
pub struct LetBinding {
    pub var: Term,
    pub value: Term,
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq)]
pub struct Lemma {
    pub name: String,
    pub modulo: Option<String>,
    pub attributes: Vec<LemmaAttr>,
    pub trace_quantifier: TraceQuantifier,
    pub formula: Formula,
    pub proof: Option<ProofSkeleton>,
    pub plaintext: String,
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq)]
pub struct DiffLemma {
    pub name: String,
    pub attributes: Vec<LemmaAttr>,
    pub proof: Option<ProofSkeleton>,
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq)]
pub struct AccLemma {
    pub name: String,
    pub attributes: Vec<LemmaAttr>,
    pub formula: Formula,
    pub case_test_idents: Vec<String>,
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq)]
pub struct CaseTest {
    pub name: String,
    pub formula: Formula,
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq)]
pub enum TraceQuantifier {
    AllTraces,
    ExistsTrace,
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq)]
pub enum LemmaAttr {
    Sources,
    Reuse,
    DiffReuse,
    UseInduction,
    HideLemma(String),
    Heuristic(String),
    Output(Vec<String>),
    Left,
    Right,
    Hint(String),
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq)]
pub struct ProofSkeleton {
    pub raw: String,
    pub tree: Option<ParsedProofTree>,
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq)]
pub struct ParsedProofTree {
    pub method: ParsedMethod,
    pub cases: Vec<(String, ParsedProofTree)>,
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq)]
pub enum ParsedMethod {
    Sorry,
    Contradiction,
    Simplify,
    Induction,
    SolveGoal(GoalSpec, String),
    SolvedLeaf,
    Unfinishable,
    Invalidated,
    Other(String),
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq)]
pub enum GoalSpec {
    Action {
        fact: Fact,
        time_var: String,
        time_idx: u32,
    },
    Premise {
        fact: Fact,
        prem_idx: usize,
        time_var: String,
        time_idx: u32,
    },
    Disj { alts: Vec<DisjAlt>, alt_texts: Vec<String> },
    Chain {
        src_var: String,
        conc_idx: u32,
        tgt_var: String,
        prem_idx: u32,
    },
    Subterm { small_raw: String, big_raw: String },
    Split { split_id: i64 },
    Raw(String),
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq, Eq)]
pub enum DisjAlt {
    All { n_vars: usize },
    Ex { n_vars: usize },
    NonQuant,
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq)]
pub struct Tactic {
    pub name: String,
    pub raw: String,
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq)]
pub struct ProcessDef {
    pub name: String,
    pub vars: Option<Vec<VarSpec>>,
    pub body: Process,
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq)]
pub enum Process {
    Null,
    Action {
        action: SapicAction,
        body: Box<Process>,
    },
    Comb {
        comb: ProcessComb,
        left: Box<Process>,
        right: Box<Process>,
    },
    Replication(Box<Process>),
    Call { name: String, args: Vec<Term> },
    AtAnnotation(Box<Process>, Term),
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq)]
pub enum SapicAction {
    New(VarSpec),
    Insert(Term, Term),
    Delete(Term),
    ChIn { chan: Option<Term>, msg: Term },
    ChOut { chan: Option<Term>, msg: Term },
    Lock(Term),
    Unlock(Term),
    Event(Fact),
    Msr { prems: Vec<Fact>, acts: Vec<Fact>, concs: Vec<Fact>, restrictions: Vec<Formula> },
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq)]
pub enum ProcessComb {
    Parallel,
    Ndc,
    Cond(Condition),
    Lookup(Term, VarSpec),
    Let { pat: Term, value: Term },
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq)]
pub enum Condition {
    Eq(Term, Term),
    Formula(Formula),
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq)]
pub struct Fact {
    pub persistent: bool,
    pub name: String,
    pub args: Vec<Term>,
    pub annotations: Vec<FactAnnotation>,
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq, Hash)]
pub enum FactAnnotation {
    SolveFirst,
    SolveLast,
    NoSources,
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq)]
pub enum Formula {
    False,
    True,
    Atom(Atom),
    Not(Box<Formula>),
    And(Box<Formula>, Box<Formula>),
    Or(Box<Formula>, Box<Formula>),
    Implies(Box<Formula>, Box<Formula>),
    Iff(Box<Formula>, Box<Formula>),
    Forall(Vec<VarSpec>, Box<Formula>),
    Exists(Vec<VarSpec>, Box<Formula>),
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq)]
pub enum Atom {
    Eq(Term, Term),
    Less(Term, Term),
    LessMset(Term, Term),
    Subterm(Term, Term),
    Action(Fact, Term),
    Last(Term),
    Pred(Fact),
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq)]
pub enum Term {
    Var(VarSpec),
    PubLit(String),
    FreshLit(String),
    NatLit(String),
    Number(u64),
    NumberOne,
    NatOne,
    DhNeutral,
    App(String, Vec<Term>),
    AlgApp(String, Box<Term>, Box<Term>),
    Pair(Vec<Term>),
    Diff(Box<Term>, Box<Term>),
    BinOp(BinOp, Box<Term>, Box<Term>),
    PatMatch(Box<Term>),
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq, Hash)]
pub enum BinOp {
    Exp,
    Mult,
    Union,
    Xor,
    NatPlus,
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq, Eq, Hash)]
pub struct VarSpec {
    pub name: String,
    pub idx: u64,
    pub sort: SortHint,
    pub typ: Option<String>,
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq, Hash, Default)]
pub enum SortHint {
    Msg,
    Pub,
    Fresh,
    Node,
    Nat,
    Suffix(SuffixSort),
    #[default]
    Untagged,
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq, Hash)]
pub enum SuffixSort { Msg, Pub, Fresh, Node, Nat }

#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq)]
pub enum FlagFormula {
    Atom(String),
    Not(Box<FlagFormula>),
    And(Box<FlagFormula>, Box<FlagFormula>),
    Or(Box<FlagFormula>, Box<FlagFormula>),
}

1	//! R3 — trace-formula rendering (shared by restrictions and lemma statements).
2	//!
3	//! Every glyph and layout decision is oracle-pinned (see workspace/BEHAVIOR.md
4	//! "Formula rendering" for probe provenance). Shape summary:
5	//!
6	//! * glyphs: `∀ ∃ ⇒ ∧ ∨ ¬ ⇔ ⊤ ⊥`, atoms `@ < = ⊏ last(..)`;
7	//! * EVERY operand of a binary connective and every `¬` argument is
8	//!   parenthesized; quantifier bodies and the top level are bare; chains
9	//!   keep their source association (probe:q_p2);
10	//! * binary connective = `sep [lhs <+> glyph, rhs]` — the glyph attaches to
11	//!   the lhs' last line, the rhs drops to the group origin;
12	//! * quantifier = `sep [`∀ `<>fsep binders<>`.`, nest 1 body]` — binders
13	//!   fill-wrap aligned after the glyph-plus-space, the body indents one
14	//!   column past the glyph (probe:q_l2);
15	//! * atoms reuse the R2 fact and R1 term docs: `Fact( … ) @ tp` is an hsep
16	//!   (the `@ tp` never drops alone — probe:q_l5), `l = r` / `l < r` /
17	//!   `l ⊏ r` are `sep [lhs <+> glyph, rhs]` (probe:q_l4), `last(tp)` has no
18	//!   interior spaces (probe:q_at1).
19	
20	use crate::ast::{Atom, Formula, VarSpec};
21	use crate::doc::{
22	    beside_op, beside_space, char, fsep, hsep, nest, render_with, sep, text, Doc,
23	};
24	use crate::rule::fact_doc;
25	use crate::term::{self, RIBBON, WIDTH};
26	
27	/// Render one formula at the echo's layout parameters, starting at column 0
28	/// (top-level position — no enclosing parentheses).
29	pub fn render(f: &Formula) -> String {
30	    render_with(WIDTH, RIBBON, &doc(f))
31	}
32	
33	/// The formula's `Doc` in BARE position (top level or quantifier body).
34	pub(crate) fn doc(f: &Formula) -> Doc {
35	    match f {
36	        Formula::True => text("\u{22a4}"),
37	        Formula::False => text("\u{22a5}"),
38	        Formula::Atom(a) => atom_doc(a),
39	        Formula::Not(g) => beside_op(text("\u{ac}"), parens(doc(g))),
40	        Formula::And(l, r) => connective_doc(l, "\u{2227}", r),
41	        Formula::Or(l, r) => connective_doc(l, "\u{2228}", r),
42	        Formula::Implies(l, r) => connective_doc(l, "\u{21d2}", r),
43	        Formula::Iff(l, r) => connective_doc(l, "\u{21d4}", r),
44	        Formula::Forall(vs, b) => quantifier_doc("\u{2200}", vs, b),
45	        Formula::Exists(vs, b) => quantifier_doc("\u{2203}", vs, b),
46	    }
47	}
48	
49	fn parens(d: Doc) -> Doc {
50	    beside_op(beside_op(char('('), d), char(')'))
51	}
52	
53	/// `(lhs) <glyph> (rhs)` — both operands parenthesized whatever they are
54	/// (probe:q_p2); on overflow the glyph stays on the lhs' last line and the
55	/// rhs drops to the group origin (targets NSLPK3/Cronto).
56	fn connective_doc(l: &Formula, glyph: &str, r: &Formula) -> Doc {
57	    sep(vec![
58	        beside_space(parens(doc(l)), text(glyph)),
59	        parens(doc(r)),
60	    ])
61	}
62	
63	/// `∀ v1 v2 #i. body` — binders fill-wrap aligned after `∀ ` with the `.`
64	/// attached to the last one; the body sits beside on one line or drops to
65	/// (quantifier origin + 1) (probe:q_l2 bw1/bw2).
66	fn quantifier_doc(glyph: &str, vs: &[VarSpec], body: &Formula) -> Doc {
67	    let binders = fsep(vs.iter().map(|v| text(&term::var_str(v))).collect());
68	    let head = beside_op(
69	        beside_op(text(&format!("{glyph} ")), binders),
70	        char('.'),
71	    );
72	    sep(vec![head, nest(1, &doc(body))])
73	}
74	
75	fn atom_doc(a: &Atom) -> Doc {
76	    match a {
77	        Atom::Eq(l, r) => relation_doc(l, "=", r),
78	        Atom::Less(l, r) => relation_doc(l, "<", r),
79	        // UNOBSERVABLE placeholder (BEHAVIOR.md): rendered like Less; not
80	        // oracle-pinned.
81	        Atom::LessMset(l, r) => relation_doc(l, "<", r),
82	        Atom::Subterm(l, r) => relation_doc(l, "\u{228f}", r),
83	        Atom::Action(f, tp) => hsep(vec![fact_doc(f), char('@'), term::doc(tp)]),
84	        Atom::Last(tp) => beside_op(beside_op(text("last("), term::doc(tp)), char(')')),
85	        // UNOBSERVABLE placeholder (BEHAVIOR.md): predicates are expanded
86	        // upstream of the echo; rendered as a bare fact, not oracle-pinned.
87	        Atom::Pred(f) => fact_doc(f),
88	    }
89	}
90	
91	/// `lhs <glyph> rhs` for `=` / `<` / `⊏`: glyph attached to the lhs' last
92	/// line, rhs drops to the atom origin on overflow (probe:q_l4).
93	fn relation_doc(l: &crate::ast::Term, glyph: &str, r: &crate::ast::Term) -> Doc {
94	    sep(vec![
95	        beside_space(term::doc(l), text(glyph)),
96	        term::doc(r),
97	    ])
98	}
99	
100	/// Safety classification for the restriction wrapper's `// safety formula`
101	/// line: a formula is safety iff its negation-normal form contains NO
102	/// existential quantifier — msg-sort or temporal alike (probes q_s1/q_s2:
103	/// ∃ in positive polarity anywhere, including a `¬∃` antecedent that
104	/// double-negates back, defeats it; `¬∃` in conclusion and top-level `¬∃`
105	/// remain safety).
106	pub(crate) fn is_safety(f: &Formula) -> bool {
107	    !has_existential_in_nnf(f, false)
108	}
109	
110	/// Does `f` contain a quantifier that becomes existential in NNF, given the
111	/// number of enclosing negations (`negated`)?
112	fn has_existential_in_nnf(f: &Formula, negated: bool) -> bool {
113	    match f {
114	        Formula::True | Formula::False | Formula::Atom(_) => false,
115	        Formula::Not(g) => has_existential_in_nnf(g, !negated),
116	        Formula::And(l, r) | Formula::Or(l, r) => {
117	            has_existential_in_nnf(l, negated) || has_existential_in_nnf(r, negated)
118	        }
119	        Formula::Implies(l, r) => {
120	            has_existential_in_nnf(l, !negated) || has_existential_in_nnf(r, negated)
121	        }
122	        // ⇔ expands to implications in both directions, so each side occurs
123	        // in both polarities. No safety-relevant ⇔ was observable (see
124	        // BEHAVIOR.md); this is the NNF-consistent reading.
125	        Formula::Iff(l, r) => {
126	            has_existential_in_nnf(l, false)
127	                || has_existential_in_nnf(l, true)
128	                || has_existential_in_nnf(r, false)
129	                || has_existential_in_nnf(r, true)
130	        }
131	        Formula::Forall(_, b) => negated || has_existential_in_nnf(b, negated),
132	        Formula::Exists(_, b) => !negated || has_existential_in_nnf(b, negated),
133	    }
134	}
135

1	//! R3 — restriction & lemma wrappers around `crate::formula::doc`.
2	//!
3	//! Byte shapes (probe provenance in workspace/BEHAVIOR.md "Restriction
4	//! blocks" / "Lemma blocks"):
5	//!
6	//! ```text
7	//! restriction Name:
8	//!   "formula"
9	//!   // safety formula          (iff the formula classifies safety)
10	//! <blank>
11	//!   /*
12	//!   expanded formula:
13	//!   "formula"
14	//!   */
15	//! ```
16	//!
17	//! ```text
18	//! lemma Name [attr1, attr2]:
19	//!   all-traces|exists-trace "formula"     (two lines when it overflows)
20	//! /*
21	//! guarded formula characterizing all counter-examples:   (| satisfying traces)
22	//! "<guarded block — opaque input>"
23	//! */
24	//! by sorry                                (| the embedded proof, verbatim)
25	//! ```
26	
27	use crate::ast::{Guarded, Lemma, LemmaAttr, Restriction, TraceQuantifier};
28	use crate::doc::{
29	    above_op, above_plus, beside_op, fsep, nest, punctuate, render_with, sep, text, vcat, Doc,
30	};
31	use crate::formula;
32	use crate::term::{RIBBON, WIDTH};
33	
34	/// One whole restriction block (also the echo of legacy `axiom` items —
35	/// probe:q_ax1).
36	pub fn render_restriction(r: &Restriction) -> String {
37	    render_with(WIDTH, RIBBON, &restriction_doc(r))
38	}
39	
40	/// One whole lemma block: header, quantifier/statement, guarded-formula
41	/// comment (skipped when `guarded` is `None`), and the proof tail
42	/// (`by sorry` when the lemma carries no embedded proof).
43	pub fn render_lemma(l: &Lemma, guarded: Option<&Guarded>) -> String {
44	    render_with(WIDTH, RIBBON, &lemma_doc(l, guarded))
45	}
46	
47	/// `"formula"` — the quotes attach directly around the formula doc; interior
48	/// breaks land one column past the opening quote's nesting (probe:q_l2).
49	fn quoted_formula(f: &crate::ast::Formula) -> Doc {
50	    beside_op(
51	        beside_op(crate::doc::char('"'), formula::doc(f)),
52	        crate::doc::char('"'),
53	    )
54	}
55	
56	/// A verbatim multi-line input block (guarded content, embedded proofs):
57	/// one `text` line per input line, stacked at the current nesting.
58	fn verbatim_doc(s: &str) -> Doc {
59	    vcat(s.lines().map(text).collect())
60	}
61	
62	// ── restrictions ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
63	
64	fn restriction_doc(r: &Restriction) -> Doc {
65	    let mut d = above_op(
66	        text(&format!("restriction {}:", r.name)),
67	        nest(2, &quoted_formula(&r.formula)),
68	    );
69	    if formula::is_safety(&r.formula) {
70	        d = above_op(d, nest(2, &text("// safety formula")));
71	    }
72	    // One blank line, then the expanded-formula comment at col 2. The
73	    // expanded content is byte-identical to the statement in every
74	    // observation (probes q_w1/q_pred1: predicate expansion happens upstream
75	    // of BOTH renderings), so the same formula renders twice.
76	    d = above_plus(d, text(""));
77	    let comment = above_op(
78	        above_op(
79	            above_op(text("/*"), text("expanded formula:")),
80	            quoted_formula(&r.formula),
81	        ),
82	        text("*/"),
83	    );
84	    above_plus(d, nest(2, &comment))
85	}
86	
87	// ── lemmas ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
88	
89	fn lemma_doc(l: &Lemma, guarded: Option<&Guarded>) -> Doc {
90	    let mut d = above_op(header_doc(l), nest(2, &statement_doc(l)));
91	    if let Some(g) = guarded {
92	        d = above_op(d, guarded_comment_doc(l.trace_quantifier, g));
93	    }
94	    let tail = match &l.proof {
95	        None => text("by sorry"),
96	        Some(p) => verbatim_doc(p),
97	    };
98	    above_op(d, tail)
99	}
100	
101	/// `lemma Name:` or `lemma Name [attrs]:` — a space before the `[`, the
102	/// attribute list fill-wrapped aligned after it with `]:` attached to the
103	/// last item (targets 5G_AKA sqn_ue_nodecrease / sqn_ue_unique); attributes
104	/// keep source order and duplicates (probe:q_la1).
105	fn header_doc(l: &Lemma) -> Doc {
106	    if l.attributes.is_empty() {
107	        return text(&format!("lemma {}:", l.name));
108	    }
109	    let items: Vec<Doc> = l.attributes.iter().map(|a| text(&attr_str(a))).collect();
110	    beside_op(
111	        beside_op(
112	            text(&format!("lemma {} [", l.name)),
113	            fsep(punctuate(&crate::doc::char(','), items)),
114	        ),
115	        text("]:"),
116	    )
117	}
118	
119	fn attr_str(a: &LemmaAttr) -> String {
120	    match a {
121	        LemmaAttr::Sources => "sources".into(),
122	        LemmaAttr::Reuse => "reuse".into(),
123	        LemmaAttr::UseInduction => "use_induction".into(),
124	        LemmaAttr::HideLemma(n) => format!("hide_lemma={n}"),
125	        LemmaAttr::Heuristic(v) => format!("heuristic={v}"),
126	    }
127	}
128	
129	/// `all-traces "…"` / `exists-trace "…"` at nest 2 — one line when the whole
130	/// statement fits, otherwise the keyword alone with the quoted formula below
131	/// at the same column (probe:q_w1; target:Minimal_Loop one-line cases).
132	fn statement_doc(l: &Lemma) -> Doc {
133	    let kw = match l.trace_quantifier {
134	        TraceQuantifier::AllTraces => "all-traces",
135	        TraceQuantifier::ExistsTrace => "exists-trace",
136	    };
137	    sep(vec![text(kw), quoted_formula(&l.formula)])
138	}
139	
140	/// The guarded-formula comment at column 0. Header text keyed by the trace
141	/// quantifier; content is opaque pre-computed input (probe:q_w1). Failed
142	/// conversions get the alternate header with the error text indented 2
143	/// (probe:q_r1 vs. the transform's raw error spelling).
144	fn guarded_comment_doc(tq: TraceQuantifier, g: &Guarded) -> Doc {
145	    let body = match g {
146	        Guarded::Formula(content) => {
147	            let header = match tq {
148	                TraceQuantifier::AllTraces => {
149	                    "guarded formula characterizing all counter-examples:"
150	                }
151	                TraceQuantifier::ExistsTrace => {
152	                    "guarded formula characterizing all satisfying traces:"
153	                }
154	            };
155	            above_op(text(header), verbatim_doc(content))
156	        }
157	        Guarded::Failed(err) => {
158	            let indented: Vec<Doc> = err
159	                .lines()
160	                .map(|ln| {
161	                    if ln.is_empty() {
162	                        text("")
163	                    } else {
164	                        text(&format!("  {ln}"))
165	                    }
166	                })
167	                .collect();
168	            above_op(text("conversion to guarded formula failed:"), vcat(indented))
169	        }
170	    };
171	    above_op(above_op(text("/*"), body), text("*/"))
172	}
