682	/// Port of HS `checkEquationsSubtermConvergence` (Wellformedness.hs:1222-1232).
683	///
684	/// HS works on `thyEquations thy = S.toList (stRules sig)` — the SIGNATURE's
685	/// subterm-rule Set, NOT the parser-AST `equations:` blocks.  The parser-level
686	/// `tamarin_parser::wf::subterm_convergence_report` approximates this on the
687	/// parser AST but (a) keeps the source order rather than the `Ord CtxtStRule`
688	/// Set order, and (b) renders each equation on a single flat line (no
689	/// width-wrapping), because the `tamarin-parser` crate has no access to the
690	/// HughesPJ engine.  This function — living in `tamarin-theory`, which has the
691	/// elaborated `MaudeSig` plus the ported HughesPJ printer — reproduces HS
692	/// byte-for-byte:
693	///
