1084	/// HS `openProtoRule` (Rule.hs:65-72) returns `OpenProtoRule ruE ruleAC`
1085	/// where `ruleAC = []` iff `equalUpToTerms cprRuleAC cprRuleE` (i.e. the
1086	/// closed rule's AC and E forms agree on fact TAGS + lengths,
1087	/// Theory/Model/Rule.hs:887-895), else `ruleAC = [cprRuleAC]`.
1088	///
1089	/// `containsManualRuleVariants` (OpenTheory.hs:584-589) is True iff some
1090	/// (merged) rule has a non-empty `ruleAC` — i.e. some rule's `openProtoRule`
1091	/// yields the `[cprRuleAC]` branch.  `prettyClosedTheory`
1092	/// (ClosedTheory.hs:382-418, see line 383) uses that to switch the WHOLE theory to the
1093	/// "open-as-closed" renderer `prettyOpenProtoRuleAsClosedRule`
1094	/// (OpenTheory.hs:827-851), which — for the `OpenProtoRule ruE []` (empty)
1095	/// branch — emits NO `prettyLoopBreakers` line ("cannot show loop breakers
1096	/// here, as we do not have the information"), whereas the
1097	/// `OpenProtoRule _ [ruAC]` (non-empty) branch KEEPS the loop breakers.
1098	///
1099	/// This predicate is RS's per-rule mirror of "would `openProtoRule` yield a
1100	/// non-empty `ruleAC`":
1101	///   * Manual variants: a parsed `variants (modulo AC)` block on the input
1102	///     rule produces `OpenProtoRule ruE (non-empty)` directly — always
1103	///     counts, with or without `--auto-sources`.
1104	///   * `--auto-sources`: `closeTheoryWithMaude` adds the synthetic
1105	///     `AUTO_IN_*`/`AUTO_OUT_*` action facts to `cprRuleAC` ONLY (NOT
1106	///     `cprRuleE` — `addActionClosedProtoRule`, Rule.hs:186-189), so an
1107	///     AUTO-annotated rule has AC ≠ E up to fact tags → `equalUpToTerms`
1108	///     False → non-empty `ruleAC`.  AC-variant substitution itself never
1109	///     changes a fact's TAG, so the AUTO action is the only operation that
1110	///     makes `equalUpToTerms` False here; "the elaborated rule carries an
1111	///     `AUTO_*` action" is therefore exactly the auto-path discriminant.
1112	///
1113	/// Used both to compute the theory-level gate (OR over all rules) and, in
1114	/// `render_rule`, to decide whether a trivial-AC-variant rule keeps or drops
1115	/// its loop-breaker comment under the open renderer.
1116	fn rule_open_ac_nonempty(
1117	    parsed_rule: &p::Rule,
1118	    elab_rule: Option<&crate::theory::OpenProtoRule>,
1119	    auto_sources: bool,
1120	) -> bool {
1121	    // Manual `variants (modulo AC)` block on the input rule.
1122	    if !parsed_rule.variants.is_empty() {
1123	        return true;
1124	    }
1125	    if !auto_sources {
1126	        // Non-auto path: HS does NOT unfold computed variants, and every
1127	        // closed rule's AC form agrees with its E form up to terms, so
1128	        // `openProtoRule` is always the empty branch.  Computed AC variants
1129	        // do not count.
1130	        return false;
1131	    }
1132	    // Auto path: the rule's AC form differs from its E form up to tags iff it
1133	    // received an `AUTO_*` action.
1134	    match elab_rule {
1135	        None => false,
1136	        Some(r) => r.rule.actions.iter().any(|f| {
1137	            matches!(&f.tag, crate::fact::FactTag::Proto(_, name, _)
1138	                if name.starts_with("AUTO_IN_") || name.starts_with("AUTO_OUT_"))
1139	        }),
1140	    }
1141	}
